<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6b98303d-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s1144"><num value="1144">§ 1144.</num><heading> Funding</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6b98303e-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s1144/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Authorizations</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated to carry out this subchapter $2,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2022 through 2026.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6b98303f-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s1144/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Derivation</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Funds to carry out the activities under this subchapter shall be derived from amounts authorized to be appropriated pursuant to the preceding subsection that are enacted after <date date="2021-01-05">January 5, 2021</date>.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id6b983040-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/116/289/s5">Pub. L. 116–289, § 5</ref>, <date date="2021-01-05">Jan. 5, 2021</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/134/4888">134 Stat. 4888</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id6b983041-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id6b983042-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id6b983043-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was enacted as part of the Young Fishermen’s Development Act, and not as part of titles I and II of <ref href="/us/pl/89/454">Pub. L. 89–454</ref> which comprise this chapter.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
